<dl id="n36122c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36122c">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36122c"> 122(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Sunday and Saturday funds</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">There are three regular funds in London for the support of hospitals. &hellip; (2) The Metropolitan Hospital <mark>Sunday Fund</mark>, founded in 1873, draws the greater part of its revenue from collections in churches on stated occasions. (3) The Metropolitan Hospital <mark>Saturday Fund</mark> was founded in 1873, and is made up chiefly of small sums collected in places of business. <small> &ldquo;LONDON&rdquo; <a name="EBLO" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EBLO"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 946c</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
